igation of the relationship between performance and print means that it will be of interest to those who care about, watch or work in early modern performance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aShakespeare 2018. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Drama.2bisacsh  aJohn Lyly.  adramaturgical stories.  aelusive theatre.  aeuphuism.  amodern authorship.  amodern culture.  anineteenth-century.  aprinted drama.  aprose fiction.  asingle-story fiction.1 aKesson, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610186040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526101860423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526101860/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles